# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# public-offer-lane.form — a stranger may offer the body anything, and be received
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The ask (Urs, 2026-06-14): a user on a public ChatGPT / Claude / Gemini,
# just pointing at our front door, can give the network an idea, concept,
# teaching, document, or task — and then ask it anything — without knowing
# git or committing to the repo.
#
# This file names the WRITE half — how an offer is received and tended. The read
# half is already public (the substrate read doors + POST /api/substrate/form).
# The write half receives a stranger's OFFER and holds it with care; grounding it
# into the canonical body is a tending act — recognition — not an arrival.
#
# It composes parts already proven, never new machinery:
#   - offer-and-acknowledge.form  — to speak to a cell is to offer it,
#                                   acknowledged by one of nothing/0/1/node
#   - afferent-offer.fk           — the UNSOLICITED offer: a world-event
#                                   arrives unasked; the body only waits
#                                   (three-way proven, band 511)
#   - contributor.claimed=false   — the held-open attribution: an offer
#                                   from a stranger is attributed to a
#                                   placeholder until they walk in and claim it
#   - substrate ingest            — content-addressed storage; same shape
#                                   converges; nothing is overwritten (axiom-3)
#   - rate_limit middleware       — the organism's breath: cooperative pacing
#                                   already meets every public POST; a burst is
#                                   slowed, the guest stays welcome
#
# An offer is an afferent offer whose payload is a submission. It is held
# as `offered`, queryable at once, and grounded into the canonical body
# only by a tending act — never on arrival.
#
# The lifecycle is proven four-way (Go/Rust/TypeScript/fkwu) in the value lane:
#   form-stdlib/offer-lane.fk -> tests/offer-lane-band.fk -> 1111111
# The faithfulness the band pins: a submission stays an offer until tended — never
# canonical on arrival (offer-arrives is OFFERED + UNCLAIMED; canonical? is 0 until
# a ground act); grounding (OFFERED -> GROUNDED + CLAIMED) is the only path into the
# body, and it is idempotent. The node-level offer (afferent-offer.fk / offer-acknowledge.fk)
# proves the same shape in the 3-kernel substrate lane.

(public-offer-lane

  (lineage
    (named-by    urs)                               # "let a stranger offer, without git"
    (proven-by   offer-lane.fk)                     # the lifecycle, four-way (1111111)
    (offer-of    offer-and-acknowledge.form)        # the contract: offer ↦ ack
    (afferent-of afferent-offer.fk)                 # unsolicited; the body waits, never asks
    (attributed  contributor.claimed=false)         # a door held open for the stranger
    (stored-by   substrate-ingest)                  # content-addressed; converges; never overwrites
    (paced-by    rate-limit-middleware)             # the breath that slows a burst
    (read-half   form-language.md)                  # the ask half, already public
    (spoken-in   field-domain-grammars.form))       # Field Model Form, the grammar family

  # ── what arrives ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  (offer
    (from        stranger)                          # no account, no git, no key
    (payload     submission)                        # idea | concept | spec | teaching | document | task
    (carrier     "POST /api/substrate/ingest")      # the public door — a carrier; a native BML route is the north star
    (shape       markdown)                          # frontmatter + body; structure becomes recipe, prose becomes word-cells
    (unsolicited 1))                                # the body never asked; afferent-offer is the engine

  # ── how it is received and held ──────────────────────────────────────
  (held
    (status      offered)                           # offered, the welcoming lane it rests in until tended
    (claimed     false)                             # attribution is a door held open until the stranger walks in
    (queryable   1)                                 # visible at once: ?cells where status == "offered"
    (in-canonical 0)                                # rests in the welcoming lane until grounded
    (addressed   content))                          # same shape converges; offering twice is idempotent (axiom-3)

  # ── the acknowledgment (axiom-5 vocabulary, exactly one) ────────────
  (acknowledge
    (1       "received — your offer is held; here is its NodeID and handle")
    (0       "declined — outside what this door accepts (unknown domain, too large)")
    (node    "counter-offer — this shape already lives here; here is the cell it converged to")
    (nothing "silence — the pacing breath; offer again in a moment (a timeout IS nothing)"))

  # ── grounding (offered → canonical, a tended act) ───────────────────
  (ground
    (who         a-tending-cell)                    # a steward of the body, human or agent
    (reads       "?cells where status == \"offered\"")
    (senses      "shape, honesty lane, sovereignty, whether it carries vitality")
    (accepts     (status offered -> grounded))      # flips the status; the cell joins canonical reads
    (claims      (claimed false -> true))           # when the offerer walks in, the door becomes theirs
    (composts    "an offer that carries no vitality is released, with care"))

  # ── the honest next breath (closing recipes, carrier-last) ──────────
  (closing-recipes
    (receive-as-offer
      "the public door receives every submission AS an offer — status offered,
       claimed false — so the body recognises an offer as an offer; nothing is
       mistaken for the body until a cell tends it in")
    (canonical-shows-the-grounded
      "the canonical read doors show the grounded body; offers rest in the
       welcoming lane, visible to whoever comes to tend them, until grounding
       brings one in")
    (native-welcome
      "lift POST /api/substrate/ingest to a native BML offer-receiver in the
       data-driven dispatch (http-server.fk registry), so the welcome is Form")))
